# Hardware Components List

## Main Components

| Component | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Arduino Nano | Main microcontroller |
| LDR Sensors | Sunlight intensity detection |
| Servo/DC Motors | Panel movement & positioning |
| Solar PV Mini Panel | Energy collection |
| Breadboard | Circuit prototyping |
| Jumper Wires | Electrical connections |
| Power Supply/Battery | System power source |
| Mechanical Frame | Dual-axis support structure |

---

## Sensors

### LDR Sensors
Used for detecting directional sunlight intensity differences to control solar panel orientation.

Typical configuration:
- Top sensor
- Bottom sensor
- Left sensor
- Right sensor

---

## Actuation System

### Servo Motors
Used for:
- Horizontal rotation (azimuth axis)
- Vertical rotation (elevation axis)

---

## Optional Future Components

| Component | Purpose |
|---|---|
| RTC Module (DS3231) | Time-based tracking |
| ESP32 | IoT monitoring |
| WiFi Module | Wireless communication |
| INA219 Sensor | Current monitoring |
| DHT11/DHT22 | Temperature monitoring |

---

## Mechanical Structure

The tracking structure is designed to:
- Rotate along two axes
- Maintain solar panel alignment
- Support automated movement
- Allow future expansion for smart tracking features

---

## Safety Considerations

- Stable frame mounting
- Proper motor current handling
- Secure electrical connections
- Controlled movement limits
- Weather protection for outdoor testing
